proteusPy.DisulfideExtractor_mp

DisulfideExtractor.py

Purpose:

This program encapsulates the steps needed to extract disulfides from the PDB file repository, build the DisulfideLoader object, and save it into the proteusPy module data directory. This program utilizes multiprocessing to speed up the extraction process.

Processes:

  • Extract: Extract SS bonds from the PDB raw files, with a cutoff of cutoff A.
  • Build: Load the data from the extraction and save it as a compressed .pkl file.
  • Update: Copy the .pkl files to the repo.
  • Subset: Only extract and process the first 1000 Disulfides found in the PDB directory.

Author: Eric G. Suchanek, PhD. Last revision: 2025-01-01 09:17:35 -egs-

  5"""
  6`DisulfideExtractor.py`
  7
  8# Purpose:
  9This program encapsulates the steps needed to extract disulfides from the PDB file repository,
 10build the DisulfideLoader object, and save it into the proteusPy module data directory. This program
 11utilizes multiprocessing to speed up the extraction process.
 12
 13# Processes:
 14* Extract: Extract SS bonds from the PDB raw files, with a cutoff of `cutoff` A.
 15* Build: Load the data from the extraction and save it as a compressed .pkl file.
 16* Update: Copy the `.pkl` files to the repo.
 17* Subset: Only extract and process the first 1000 Disulfides found in the PDB directory.
 18
 19Author: Eric G. Suchanek, PhD.
 20Last revision: 2025-01-01 09:17:35 -egs-
 21"""

133def parse_arguments():
134    """
135    Parse command line arguments.
136    """
137
138    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(
139        description=f"""\nproteusPy Disulfide Bond Extractor v{__version__}\n
140        This program extracts disulfide bonds from PDB files and builds a DisulfideLoader object.
141        The program expects the environment variable PDB to be set to the base location of the PDB files.
142        The PDB files are expected to be in the PDB/good directory. Relevant output files, 
143        (SS_*LOADER*.pkl) are stored in PDB/data."""
144    )
145    parser.add_argument(
146        "--extract",
147        "-e",
148        action="store_true",
149        help="Extract Disulfide data",
150        default=False,
151    )
152    parser.add_argument(
153        "--build",
154        "-b",
155        action="store_true",
156        help="Build Disulfide loader",
157        default=False,
158    )
159    parser.add_argument(
160        "--update",
161        "-u",
162        action="store_true",
163        help="Update repository data directory",
164        default=False,
165    )
166    parser.add_argument(
167        "--full",
168        "-f",
169        action="store_true",
170        help="Process full SS database",
171        default=False,
172    )
173    parser.add_argument(
174        "--subset", "-s", action="store_true", help="Process SS subset", default=False
175    )
176    parser.add_argument(
177        "--verbose",
178        "-v",
179        action="store_true",
180        help="Enable verbose output",
181        default=True,
182    )
183    parser.add_argument(
184        "--cutoff",
185        "-c",
186        type=float,
187        help="Disulfide Distance Cutoff, (Angstrom)",
188        default=-1.0,
189    )
190    parser.add_argument(
191        "--threads",
192        "-t",
193        type=int,
194        help="Number of threads to use for extraction",
195        default=8,
196    )
197    parser.add_argument(
198        "--forge",
199        "-r",
200        type=str,
201        help="miniforge3 or mambaforge",
202        default="miniforge3",
203    )
204    parser.add_argument(
205        "--env",
206        "-n",
207        type=str,
208        help="ppydev or proteusPy",
209        default="ppydev",
210    )
211    parser.add_argument(
212        "--gamma",
213        "-g",
214        type=float,
215        help="Sg cutoff distance",
216        default=-1.0,
217    )
218
219    return parser.parse_args()

222def extract_disulfides_chunk(args):
223    "This is a single thread, processing one chunk of the multiprocessing extraction process."
224
225    (
226        start_idx,
227        end_idx,
228        sslist,
229        pdbdir,
230        dist_cutoff,
231        verbose,
232        quiet,
233        pbar_index,
234        sg_cutoff,
235    ) = args
236
237    result_list = []
238
239    if quiet:
240        _logger.setLevel(logging.WARNING)
241
242    entrylist = sslist[start_idx:end_idx]
243
244    task_pbar = tqdm(
245        total=len(entrylist),
246        desc=f"{Fore.BLUE}  Process {pbar_index+1:2}{Style.RESET_ALL}".ljust(10),
247        position=pbar_index + 1,
248        leave=False,
249        ncols=PBAR_COLS,
250        bar_format="{l_bar}%s{bar}{r_bar}%s" % (Fore.YELLOW, Style.RESET_ALL),
251        mininterval=1.0,
252    )
253
254    for entry in entrylist:
255        _sslist = load_disulfides_from_id(
256            entry,
257            verbose=verbose,
258            quiet=quiet,
259            pdb_dir=pdbdir,
260            cutoff=dist_cutoff,
261            sg_cutoff=sg_cutoff,
262        )
263
264        if len(_sslist) > 0:
265            sslist = remove_duplicate_ss(_sslist)
266            result_list.extend(sslist)
267
268        task_pbar.update(1)
269
270    task_pbar.close()
271    return result_list
272

274def do_extract(verbose, full, cutoff=-1.0, sg_cutoff=-1.0, nthreads=8):
275    """
276    Extracts the disulfides from the PDB files using multiprocessing.
277
278    This function processes PDB files to extract disulfide bonds. It uses multiprocessing
279    to parallelize the extraction process across multiple threads. The results are then
280    combined and saved to a pickle file.
281
282    :param verbose: If True, enables verbose output.
283    :type verbose: bool
284    :param full: If True, processes all PDB files; otherwise, processes a subset.
285    :type full: bool
286    :param cutoff: The cutoff value for filtering disulfides.
287    :type cutoff: float
288    :param prune: Not used in this function.
289    :type prune: bool
290    :param nthreads: The number of threads to use for multiprocessing. Default is 6.
291    :type nthreads: int
292    :return: None
293    """
294
295    sslist = [Path(f).stem[3:7] for f in ent_files]
296
297    if full:
298        _num_ent_files = num_ent_files
299    else:
300        _num_ent_files = 1000
301
302    chunk_size = _num_ent_files // nthreads
303    res_list = DisulfideList([], "PDB_ALL_SS")
304
305    pool_args = [
306        (
307            i * chunk_size,
308            (i + 1) * chunk_size if i != nthreads - 1 else _num_ent_files,
309            sslist,
310            PDB_DIR,
311            cutoff,
312            verbose,
313            True,
314            i,
315            sg_cutoff,
316        )
317        for i in range(nthreads)
318    ]
319
320    with multiprocessing.Pool(nthreads) as pool:
321        results = pool.map(extract_disulfides_chunk, pool_args)
322
323    if verbose:
324        print("\nProcessing results...")
325
326    for result in results:
327        res_list.extend(result)
328
329    # save the disulfides to a pickle file
330    if full:
331        if verbose:
332            print(f"Saving SS list to: {DATA_DIR / SS_PICKLE_FILE}")
333
334        with open(str(DATA_DIR / SS_PICKLE_FILE), "wb+") as f:
335            pickle.dump(res_list, f)
336
337    else:
338        if verbose:
339            print(f"Saving SS subset list to: {DATA_DIR / SS_SUBSET_PICKLE_FILE}")
340
341        with open(str(DATA_DIR / SS_SUBSET_PICKLE_FILE), "wb+") as f:
342            pickle.dump(res_list, f)
343
344
345def do_build(verbose, full, subset, cutoff, sg_cutoff):
346    """
347    Load and save a ```proteusPy.DisulfideLoader``` object
348    to a .pkl file.
349
350    :param verbose: Verbosity, boolean
351    :param full: Whether to load and save the full dataset, boolean
352    :param subset: Whether to load and save the subset database, boolean
353    """
354
355    if full:
356        if verbose:
357            print(
358                f"Building the compressed loader for the full dataset with cutoffs: Cα: {cutoff}Å, Sγ: {sg_cutoff}Å"
359            )
360        PDB_SS = DisulfideLoader(
361            datadir=DATA_DIR,
362            subset=False,
363            verbose=verbose,
364            cutoff=cutoff,
365            sg_cutoff=sg_cutoff,
366        )
367        PDB_SS.save(
368            savepath=DATA_DIR, subset=subset, cutoff=cutoff, sg_cutoff=sg_cutoff
369        )
370
371    elif subset:
372        if verbose:
373            print(
374                f"Building the packed loader for the Disulfide subset with cutoffs: {cutoff}, {sg_cutoff}..."
375            )
376        PDB_SS = DisulfideLoader(
377            datadir=DATA_DIR,
378            subset=True,
379            verbose=verbose,
380            cutoff=cutoff,
381            sg_cutoff=sg_cutoff,
382        )
383        PDB_SS.save(
384            savepath=DATA_DIR, subset=subset, cutoff=cutoff, sg_cutoff=sg_cutoff
385        )
386    else:
387        print("Error: No valid build option selected.")
388        sys.exit(1)
389
390    PDB_SS.describe()
391
392
393def update_repo(datadir, destdir):
394    """
395    Updates the repository with the latest SS files.
396    """
397
398    copy(Path(datadir) / LOADER_FNAME, Path(destdir))
399    copy(Path(datadir) / LOADER_SUBSET_FNAME, Path(destdir))
400    copy(Path(datadir) / SS_PICKLE_FILE, Path(destdir))
401    copy(Path(datadir) / SS_SUBSET_PICKLE_FILE, Path(destdir))
402
403
404def do_stuff(
405    extract=False,
406    build=False,
407    full=False,
408    update=False,
409    subset=False,
410    verbose=False,
411    cutoff=-1.0,
412    threads=8,
413    forge="miniforge3",
414    env="ppydev",
415    sg_cutoff=-1.0,
416):
417    """
418    Main entrypoint for the proteusPy Disulfide database extraction and creation workflow.
419
420    :param all: Extract the full database, defaults to False
421    :param extract: Perform extaction from raw PDB files, defaults to False
422    :param build: Build the loader(s), defaults to True
423    :param full: Build the full loader, defaults to False
424    :param update: Update the repo, defaults to True
425    :param subset: Extract the subset, defaults to True
426    :param verbose: Be noisy, defaults to True
427    :param cutoff: Distance cutoff (A), defaults to -1.0 for full extract
428    """
429    _extract = extract
430    _build = build
431    _full = full
432    _update = update
433    _subset = subset
434    _verbose = verbose
435    _threads = threads
436    _forge = forge
437    _env = env
438    _cutoff = cutoff
439
440    _master = bool(_cutoff < 0.0)
441
442    if _extract is True:
443        do_extract(
444            verbose=_verbose,
445            full=_full,
446            cutoff=cutoff,
447            sg_cutoff=sg_cutoff,
448            nthreads=_threads,
449        )
450        print("\n")
451
452    if _build is True:
453        if verbose:
454            if _master:
455                print("Building master loader since cutoff is negative.")
456            else:
457                print(f"Building with Ca cutoff: {cutoff}, Sg cutoff: {sg_cutoff}")
458        do_build(_verbose, _full, _subset, cutoff, sg_cutoff)
459
460    if _update is True:
461
462        if _forge == "miniforge3":
463            venv_dir = MINIFORGE_DIR / _env / VENV_DIR
464        else:
465            venv_dir = MAMBAFORGE_DIR / _env / VENV_DIR
466
467        if verbose:
468            print(f"Copying SS files from: {DATA_DIR} to {venv_dir}")
469
470        update_repo(DATA_DIR, venv_dir)
471
472    return
473

475def clear_screen():
476    """
477    Clears the terminal screen.
478    """
479    if os.name == "nt":  # For Windows
480        os.system("cls")
481    else:  # For macOS and Linux
482        os.system("clear")
483
484
485def main():
486    "Main entrypoint for the DisulfideExtractor program."
487    clear_screen()
488    start = time.time()
489    args = parse_arguments()
490
491    # set_logging_level_for_all_handlers(logging.ERROR)
492    # toggle_stream_handler("proteusPy.ssparser", False)
493
494    # set_logging_level_for_all_handlers(logging.ERROR)
495    # disable_stream_handlers_for_namespace("proteusPy")
496
497    _logger.info("Starting DisulfideExtractor at time %s", datetime.datetime.now())
498
499    mess = (
500        f"proteusPy DisulfideExtractor v{__version__}\n"
501        f"PDB model directory:       {PDB_DIR}\n"
502        f"Data directory:            {DATA_DIR}\n"
503        f"Module data directory:     {MODULE_DATA}\n"
504        f"Repo data directory:       {REPO_DATA}\n"
505        f"Number of .ent files:      {num_ent_files}\n"
506        f"Cα cutoff:                 {args.cutoff}\n"
507        f"Sγ cutoff:                 {args.gamma}\n"
508        f"Extract:                   {args.extract}\n"
509        f"Build:                     {args.build}\n"
510        f"Update:                    {args.update}\n"
511        f"Full:                      {args.full}\n"
512        f"Subset:                    {args.subset}\n"
513        f"Verbose:                   {args.verbose}\n"
514        f"Threads:                   {args.threads}\n"
515        f"Forge:                     {args.forge}\n"
516        f"Environment:               {args.env}\n"
517        f"Starting at:               {datetime.datetime.now()}\n"
518    )
519
520    _logger.info(mess)
521
522    do_stuff(
523        extract=args.extract,
524        build=args.build,
525        update=args.update,
526        full=args.full,
527        subset=args.subset,
528        verbose=args.verbose,
529        cutoff=args.cutoff,
530        threads=args.threads,
531        forge=args.forge,
532        env=args.env,
533        sg_cutoff=args.gamma,
534    )
535
536    end = time.time()
537
538    elapsed_time = timedelta(seconds=end - start)
539
540    hours, remainder = divmod(elapsed_time.total_seconds(), 3600)
541    minutes, seconds = divmod(remainder, 60)
542    print(f"Processing completed in {int(hours)}h:{int(minutes)}m:{int(seconds)}")
543
544
545if __name__ == "__main__":
546    main()
547
548    print(f"Finished DisulfideExtraction at time %s", datetime.datetime.now())
549

def extract_disulfides_chunk(args): 
223def extract_disulfides_chunk(args):
224    "This is a single thread, processing one chunk of the multiprocessing extraction process."
225
226    (
227        start_idx,
228        end_idx,
229        sslist,
230        pdbdir,
231        dist_cutoff,
232        verbose,
233        quiet,
234        pbar_index,
235        sg_cutoff,
236    ) = args
237
238    result_list = []
239
240    if quiet:
241        _logger.setLevel(logging.WARNING)
242
243    entrylist = sslist[start_idx:end_idx]
244
245    task_pbar = tqdm(
246        total=len(entrylist),
247        desc=f"{Fore.BLUE}  Process {pbar_index+1:2}{Style.RESET_ALL}".ljust(10),
248        position=pbar_index + 1,
249        leave=False,
250        ncols=PBAR_COLS,
251        bar_format="{l_bar}%s{bar}{r_bar}%s" % (Fore.YELLOW, Style.RESET_ALL),
252        mininterval=1.0,
253    )
254
255    for entry in entrylist:
256        _sslist = load_disulfides_from_id(
257            entry,
258            verbose=verbose,
259            quiet=quiet,
260            pdb_dir=pdbdir,
261            cutoff=dist_cutoff,
262            sg_cutoff=sg_cutoff,
263        )
264
265        if len(_sslist) > 0:
266            sslist = remove_duplicate_ss(_sslist)
267            result_list.extend(sslist)
268
269        task_pbar.update(1)
270
271    task_pbar.close()
272    return result_list

This is a single thread, processing one chunk of the multiprocessing extraction process.

def do_extract(verbose, full, cutoff=-1.0, sg_cutoff=-1.0, nthreads=8): 
275def do_extract(verbose, full, cutoff=-1.0, sg_cutoff=-1.0, nthreads=8):
276    """
277    Extracts the disulfides from the PDB files using multiprocessing.
278
279    This function processes PDB files to extract disulfide bonds. It uses multiprocessing
280    to parallelize the extraction process across multiple threads. The results are then
281    combined and saved to a pickle file.
282
283    :param verbose: If True, enables verbose output.
284    :type verbose: bool
285    :param full: If True, processes all PDB files; otherwise, processes a subset.
286    :type full: bool
287    :param cutoff: The cutoff value for filtering disulfides.
288    :type cutoff: float
289    :param prune: Not used in this function.
290    :type prune: bool
291    :param nthreads: The number of threads to use for multiprocessing. Default is 6.
292    :type nthreads: int
293    :return: None
294    """
295
296    sslist = [Path(f).stem[3:7] for f in ent_files]
297
298    if full:
299        _num_ent_files = num_ent_files
300    else:
301        _num_ent_files = 1000
302
303    chunk_size = _num_ent_files // nthreads
304    res_list = DisulfideList([], "PDB_ALL_SS")
305
306    pool_args = [
307        (
308            i * chunk_size,
309            (i + 1) * chunk_size if i != nthreads - 1 else _num_ent_files,
310            sslist,
311            PDB_DIR,
312            cutoff,
313            verbose,
314            True,
315            i,
316            sg_cutoff,
317        )
318        for i in range(nthreads)
319    ]
320
321    with multiprocessing.Pool(nthreads) as pool:
322        results = pool.map(extract_disulfides_chunk, pool_args)
323
324    if verbose:
325        print("\nProcessing results...")
326
327    for result in results:
328        res_list.extend(result)
329
330    # save the disulfides to a pickle file

Extracts the disulfides from the PDB files using multiprocessing.

This function processes PDB files to extract disulfide bonds. It uses multiprocessing to parallelize the extraction process across multiple threads. The results are then combined and saved to a pickle file.

Parameters
  • verbose: If True, enables verbose output.
  • full: If True, processes all PDB files; otherwise, processes a subset.
  • cutoff: The cutoff value for filtering disulfides.
  • prune: Not used in this function.
  • nthreads: The number of threads to use for multiprocessing. Default is 6.
Returns

None

347    """
348    Load and save a ```proteusPy.DisulfideLoader``` object
349    to a .pkl file.
350
351    :param verbose: Verbosity, boolean
352    :param full: Whether to load and save the full dataset, boolean
353    :param subset: Whether to load and save the subset database, boolean
354    """
355
356    if full:

359                f"Building the compressed loader for the full dataset with cutoffs: Cα: {cutoff}Å, Sγ: {sg_cutoff}Å"
360            )
361        PDB_SS = DisulfideLoader(
362            datadir=DATA_DIR,
363            subset=False,
364            verbose=verbose,
365            cutoff=cutoff,
366            sg_cutoff=sg_cutoff,
367        )
368        PDB_SS.save(

370        )
371
372    elif subset:
373        if verbose:
374            print(

376            )
377        PDB_SS = DisulfideLoader(
378            datadir=DATA_DIR,
379            subset=True,
380            verbose=verbose,
381            cutoff=cutoff,
382            sg_cutoff=sg_cutoff,
383        )
384        PDB_SS.save(
385            savepath=DATA_DIR, subset=subset, cutoff=cutoff, sg_cutoff=sg_cutoff
386        )
387    else:
388        print("Error: No valid build option selected.")
389        sys.exit(1)

def do_stuff( extract=False, build=False, full=False, update=False, subset=False, verbose=False, cutoff=-1.0, threads=8, forge='miniforge3', env='ppydev', sg_cutoff=-1.0): 
405def do_stuff(
406    extract=False,
407    build=False,
408    full=False,
409    update=False,
410    subset=False,
411    verbose=False,
412    cutoff=-1.0,
413    threads=8,
414    forge="miniforge3",
415    env="ppydev",
416    sg_cutoff=-1.0,
417):
418    """
419    Main entrypoint for the proteusPy Disulfide database extraction and creation workflow.
420
421    :param all: Extract the full database, defaults to False
422    :param extract: Perform extaction from raw PDB files, defaults to False
423    :param build: Build the loader(s), defaults to True
424    :param full: Build the full loader, defaults to False
425    :param update: Update the repo, defaults to True
426    :param subset: Extract the subset, defaults to True
427    :param verbose: Be noisy, defaults to True
428    :param cutoff: Distance cutoff (A), defaults to -1.0 for full extract
429    """
430    _extract = extract
431    _build = build
432    _full = full
433    _update = update
434    _subset = subset
435    _verbose = verbose
436    _threads = threads
437    _forge = forge
438    _env = env
439    _cutoff = cutoff
440
441    _master = bool(_cutoff < 0.0)
442
443    if _extract is True:
444        do_extract(
445            verbose=_verbose,
446            full=_full,
447            cutoff=cutoff,
448            sg_cutoff=sg_cutoff,
449            nthreads=_threads,
450        )
451        print("\n")
452
453    if _build is True:
454        if verbose:
455            if _master:
456                print("Building master loader since cutoff is negative.")
457            else:
458                print(f"Building with Ca cutoff: {cutoff}, Sg cutoff: {sg_cutoff}")
459        do_build(_verbose, _full, _subset, cutoff, sg_cutoff)
460
461    if _update is True:
462
463        if _forge == "miniforge3":
464            venv_dir = MINIFORGE_DIR / _env / VENV_DIR
465        else:
466            venv_dir = MAMBAFORGE_DIR / _env / VENV_DIR
467
468        if verbose:
469            print(f"Copying SS files from: {DATA_DIR} to {venv_dir}")
470
471        update_repo(DATA_DIR, venv_dir)
472
473    return

  • update: Update the repo, defaults to True
